Date: 5 May 89 16:55:23 GMT
From: mdk@beach.cis.ufl.edu  (Marji Klugerman)
Subject: Period names and Personas
Message-Id: <20255@uflorida.cis.ufl.EDU>

Unto Luwenth the Leud, fair greeting from Majir the Blatant! ;)

I suppose the best place to start is to say, Hey! slow down a second.
It's been said before, I'll say it once more - you are only *required*
(and even that might be too strong a word) to make an *attempt* at
period garb.  Nothing about names or personas.  It took me 5 years to
settle on a period name and persona.  It wasn't that important to me
before then.  When I decided it was time to create one, it just all
fell together from all the things I learned and all the opinions I
developed those first five years.  A little research filled out the
details and pulled it together.

The name I finally chose is Marie Eve Clouet and yes, it is different from
Majir the Blatant.  When I arrived at my first even, I was asked "What do
we call you?"  I wanted to be called something different than my real name
but something close enough to it that I would recognize when someone was
calling to me.  Majir is just Marji with the letters switched.  It's made
up, absolutely and completely.  I TRIED to find some *real, period* name
that came close to it and failed.  When I was apprenticed not too long ago,
I was called up in court as Marie Eve - but I will *always* be known as
Majir.  One can even take the case one step further - My first name is
Marjorie but I can't tell you the last time anyone called me that.  It's
usually Marj or Marji.  Legally, i.e., driver's license and pay checks, 
I am Marjorie.

As for how serious your persona gets, that's up to you.  I wear the style
of clothes that an upper class/noble woman living in the late 1500s, early
1600s would wear.  I suppose if I fought, I would attempt to wear the
armor that would have been used at that time as well.  However, while
I have two younger sisters, Marie Eve has two older brothers and no sisters
at all.  Those brothers are purely imaginary - I have no friends in the
SCA whose personas are those of Marie Eve's brothers.  One of my sisters
is in the SCA, within the same barony at that, but there is no relation
between her persona and mine.

Creating a solid, period persona is a lot of work for ANYONE in the SCA,
old or new.  "Oldcomers" just know the research ropes a little better, I
suppose.  I suppose it also depends on whether you want a serious persona
or a less serious, social type.  Majir the Blatant has a bit of persona,
but it doesn't hold much water...

I think it would be nice if we could make up our own names and such (I
really like the name Majir) but who becomes the arbiter of what maintains
period ambience and what doesn't?  By limiting name registration to what
can be documented, we escape a lot of problems.  I think that this is the
most practical thing to do.

So relax a little, Luwenth.  You don't get kicked out of the SCA if you
don't have a water-tight persona worked up in six months :-)  It's also
much more satisfying if you create a persona because _you want to_ than
because someone expects it of you.  Pardon the expression, but you're the
one who has to sleep with it...

Yours in long-winded service,

Lady Marie Eve Clouet
or just li'l `ol me, Majir the Blatant


