RE : Landed Barons are forever.
	Not in the Rhydderich Hael.  You serve four years and run for 
re-election.  As far as we're concerned, it's just another Baronial office.

RE : Poster said favors from one man to another probably exist, but she's
never seen one.
	I have.  I wear one.  It's called a squire's belt.  Think about it.
It's been pretty much determined that favors can take nearly any physical
form although most of them are worn, be given/worn for nearly any length of 
time and represent nearly any kind of a relationship.  Having a squire's belt 
bestows no order of precedence on the wearer, nor does it admit him/her into 
any order.  There is definitely a relationship between knight and squire, 
although there are probably as many definitions of it as there are 
knight-squire relationships in the SCA.  All we've done is take one, specific
form (the red belt) and indicate that it represents one, specific type of
relationship.
	However, as long as people are discussing favor stories.... 
The lady Aelis is blind.  Most of the people in our barony make enough noise
when they walk that not only can Aelis can tell when someone is approaching
but in most cases can actually identify who it is.  I seem to be one of 
the exceptions.  I move quietly enough that I have, on occasion, startled
her.  Her solution?  She gave me a favor of friendship to wear.  It has bells 
on it!  (meow?)

RE : Poster speculated on whether some sort of gambling arrangement could
be instituted around a tourney.
	The East Kingdom's been doing it for years at their Crown Tourneys.
Details to follow in later (and much longer) posting when I have the time
unless someone else beats me to it.

