Greetings!

The second draft of the new Rules for Heraldic Submissions has been
mailed to the College of Arms for commentary.  I will be sending
copies to commenting heralds in the East, and I suspect some other
Principal Heralds will do the same in their kingdoms.  If you wish to
get a copy and comment on it, I urge you to contact your principal
herald.  The more commentary Mistress Alisoun receives the better the
final rules will be.  This draft is scheduled for about 6 weeks of
review, after which a second draft will be issued for final review &
comment.  The new rules will be presented ot the BoD for their
approval at the October meeting.

The new rules represents a substantial simplification and
re-organization of the existing rules.  Many special cases have been
eliminated or merged into existing rules, and the document as a whole
is much more readable.  The most significant simplification is the
wholescale elimination of the major/minor point method of counting
difference between pieces of armory. It has been replaced by a system
which requires two differences, each of which would have been
sufficient for primary cadency in periuod heraldry.  The draft of the
rules proposes a list of the types of changes which would count as
such differences.  No more must every pursuivant take a course in
differential heraldic calculus!

I will try to get a copy of the text of the rules onto the net.  If I
do, I will let you all know, and will be happy to mail out copies.

