Vnend's method of training a new fighter is almost the opposite of
what I am used to.  Normally "we" (whoever that is) get a new
fighter used to weapons/shields long before they ever get into
armor.

The Bay Area (Pric. of the Mists) has two (or more) "slow work"
classes, where new fighters are taught the basics of stance,
movement, throwing shots, blocking, etc.  All this before they get
into armor.  Basically, the idea is to teach them the basics while
they are "getting their armor together".  Hopefully, they will be
less confused when they do get into armor.

Also, a lot of people drop out before they ever get into armor.
This keeps them from needing to get armor together, and saves the
trainers from having to train them in armor.

It sounds like Vnend's method work fine.  But it may not work as
well with groups of people, or when there is a high drop out rate.

