Subject: multiple personas

About multiple personas - I agree that they seldom work.  However, I have
seen them work magnificently.  The real key would seem to be the dedication
of the person in researching and playing the part.  I fully intend to have
at least two personas, but not until I have spent the time and effort to
develop two separate, distinguishable characters.  I don't even have one
persona, yet - which may give you some idea of how much effort I consider
necessary for a persona (I've been in the SCA for 7 years - dormant for
2 1/2 of those 7).

I think multiple personas are valuable - if only to demonstrate what a
persona should be.  Most people seem to play themselves in a different
time, interacting with other people playing themselves.  The really good
ones I have seen play carefully constructed characters, and can carry off
multiples.

Ariel - to avoid "Ariel in a kimono", you might find visualization exercises
helpful.  Rehearse your name and your behavior pre-event, on the drive to
event, and in spare moments at the event.  You may find you want more research
into manners, etc., but I wouldn't let that keep you from enjoying multiple
personae.  People will go along with the role you play, but it takes a lot
of effort for you to set that role for them.

Eleanor MacNaughton
