Old errors stick!
There are still those who are commenting on my first posting about "same
sex consorts". That posting was unclear and badly phrased, and I have later
posted another one where I tried to make myself clearer. Since this has
obviously not reached everyone, let me repeat some of the contents.

I do not intend to debate the issue of the ethical validity of homosexuality
on the SCA-net, because it doesn't belong here. I fear such a discussion
would become an endless series of flames (like hell). I therefore refrain
from answering those who have questioned my views on that matter. Write
personal email to me if you want to discuss it further.

All I was trying to say was that consorts of the same sex would make the
throne a platform for gay liberation (if the King and consort were openly
homosexual lovers). Swearing fealty in such a reign would signify an open
acceptance of homosexual activities and relationships. I think that all such
personal matters should be kept off the thrones. If the king/queen used 
the throne as a platform for preaching a certain religion or political
ideology, I would find that also distasteful.

I have no problem with gay people, but I refuse to perform any action
that would signify acceptance of homosexual activities. I expect gay people
to respect my beliefs on this matter, as a matter of courtesy if nothing else.

