To make one small addition to Mistress Niccola's fine comments on
documentation - a simple way to keep track of where your photocopies
came from is to photocopy the title page of the book too.  Having
said it, this will no doubt seem obvious, but it is absolutely
amazing how many people never think of it on their own.  After
doing my photocopying (including title page, and often bibliography)
I staple the entire set into one packet and add it to the file folder
for whatever subject I'm researching at the moment.  When I want
the originals, I can track them down quickly and easily.

