Subject:  Combat Sheep Rugby, aka Buzkashi

In SCA Digest #302, Chelidon o Gaerddrych (hoffman@gondor.cs.psu.edu
(Richard C. Hoffman)) writes about "Combat Sheep Rugby".

In Ealdormere, we know this game as Buzkashi, spellings vary. Buzkashi is
the Afghan national sport and a precursor of polo. Real Buzkashi is
played by armed and armoured horsemen, using a real dead sheep. And real
weapons! See the first episode of "The Ascent of Man".

For the Eoforwic "East meets West" event, about ten years ago, Baron
Torbin of Amberhall devised the first SCA Buzkashi rules. Single swords,
the sheep may be used as a shield. There are no teams - the last man
holding the sheep as it rounds the second pole scores the point for the
game. There is honour in carrying the sheep, even if it gets you killed.
Resurrection applies, of course. The sheep's name is Murphy (in Eoforwic)
or Fuscia (in Skraeling Althing).

